{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "module": "commonjs",
    "target": "ES2022",
    /**
     * DOM is here for `fetch`, not for a browser — and it is load-bearing.
     *
     * `@types/node` declares the fetch globals conditionally (`web-globals/fetch.d.ts`):
     *
     *   type _Response = typeof globalThis extends { onmessage: any } ? {} : undici.Response;
     *   interface Response extends _Response {}
     *
     * It assumes whatever supplied `onmessage` — i.e. `lib.dom` — also supplies a real
     * `Response`. Anything that supplies `onmessage` *without* a DOM lib breaks that assumption:
     * `Response`, `RequestInit`, `Headers` and `FormData` all collapse to `{}`, and every
     * `.ok`/`.status`/`.json()`/`.text()` in this codebase stops compiling — 84 errors, in files
     * nobody touched. That is what building this app on Vercel did and a local build never did,
     * on the same commit and the same lockfile (`@types/node` 22.20.1 both sides); neither a
     * clean `--frozen-lockfile` clone nor a fresh `nest build` reproduces it here, so the trigger
     * is in the build image and is not something this repo can pin.
     *
     * Including DOM settles it in either environment, because DOM itself declares `onmessage`:
     * the guard always takes its intended branch and DOM always supplies the real shapes. The
     * cost is that DOM's `BlobPart`/`BodyInit` do not accept a Node `Buffer`, so the few places
     * that build a `Blob` or a request body wrap it in `new Uint8Array(...)` — which
     * `social/providers.ts` already did.
     */
    "lib": ["ES2022", "DOM"],
    /** Only @types/node is auto-included, so a stray @types package cannot change what compiles. */
    "types": ["node"],
    "declaration": false,
    "removeComments": true,
    "emitDecoratorMetadata": true,
    "experimentalDecorators": true,
    "allowSyntheticDefaultImports": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "sourceMap": true,
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "baseUrl": "./",
    "incremental": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "strict": true,
    "strictPropertyInitialization": false,
    "forceConsistentCasingInFileNames": true,
    "resolveJsonModule": true
  },
  "include": ["src", "test", "api", "prisma/seed.ts"],
  "exclude": ["node_modules", "dist"]
}
